PRO wins on superior evidence grounding, more effective clash, and clearer impact weighing. PRO's central argument about irreversibility is never adequately answered by CON. While CON raises legitimate points about mineral needs, they fail to demonstrate why these needs justify the permanent destruction PRO describes, especially when PRO offers alternatives. The debate hinges on whether speculative future regulations can prevent irreversible harm—PRO wins this clash by emphasizing the permanence of ecosystem destruction versus CON's reliance on unproven mitigation.

